## Relationship To The Meridian AI Standard

The Meridian AI Standard is now maintained as a peer public project at [meridianstandard.ai](https://meridianstandard.ai), with its own repository at [keplertau/Meridian-AI-Standard](https://github.com/keplertau/Meridian-AI-Standard). Its repository and site carry their own license notices.

This repository may refer to the AI Standard, but it is not the Standard's active source repository.

## Why This License Structure

The Codex is open because the work it teaches cannot be held behind a gate without contradicting itself. A framework for honest inquiry, clear sight, and cooperation should be readable, reusable, criticizable, and adaptable.

Attribution matters because the Codex is a living document. It evolves, corrects itself, and keeps a public record of its revisions. A clear path back to the source lets readers compare an excerpt, adaptation, translation, or derivative framework against the current original.

The license is not a fence around the work. It is the rule that keeps the source visible while letting the work travel.
